---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  description="Aadi Labs is building self-improving, pluralistically aligned intelligence: the last intelligence software you'll ever need, useful from day one without a learning curve."
>
  <main class="container" role="main">
    <section class="content">
      <p>
        Most AI today is built to replace people, not augment them.
        We're building the opposite: AI for higher agency and bigger
        ambition. Software that makes one person more capable, not less
        necessary. AI that self-improves and collaborates with you to
        reach what neither could alone.
      </p>

      <h2>Models are not products.</h2>

      <p>
        Today's AI products don't self-improve. The model is frozen the
        day it ships. The harness around it is static. Memory features
        store facts to look up later, which is useful but not learning.
        The system doesn't get sharper because you used it yesterday.
      </p>

      <p>
        A truly intelligent product would do the opposite. The model
        would be invisible. The product would learn from real use,
        evolve to fit the specific person using it, and get sharper
        every day on its own.
      </p>

      <h2>The bet: continual learning and pluralistic alignment</h2>

      <p>
        Two research bets sit underneath everything we ship.
        <strong>Continual learning</strong>: systems that keep getting
        sharper from real production experience, without regressing on
        what they already got right. <strong>Pluralistic alignment</strong>:
        staying true to the specific person or organization they serve,
        not to a population average.
      </p>

      <h2>We own the stack.</h2>

      <p>
        We're not a wrapper around someone else's API. The whole stack,
        from product to research, is ours. That lets us take bets other
        labs won't, change direction when the evidence demands it, and
        put every interaction to work twice: serving the user now, and
        training what comes next.
      </p>

      <p>
        While we research the next sample-efficient pretraining
        architecture, we're productionizing the leading edges of
        sleep-time and test-time compute, context engineering, and RL
        research to bring a self-improving, distinctive intelligence
        product to market.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this matters</h2>

      <p>
        We are not building AI to replace people. We are building it to
        let them aim higher. The honest version of intelligence at this
        scale is human-AI co-evolution: the system gets sharper the
        longer you use it, and you get more capable the longer you have
        it. The relationship is the unit of progress.
      </p>

      <p>
        A lot of capability and creativity is local. One person, one
        community, one tradition of craft. Most of it never compounds
        into anything visible because the leverage isn't there.
        Ramanujan almost didn't reach the world. The next decade of AI
        is the difference between finding the next one and never knowing
        they existed.
      </p>

      <p>
        Done right, this kind of software is how distributed human
        intelligence finally compounds. Done wrong, it's how we lose it.
        That's the bet, and that's why we're building Aadi Labs.
      </p>

      <p>
        A small, mission-driven team, in this for the long haul.
      </p>

      <h2>Two products. One engine.</h2>

      <div class="products">
        <article class="product">
          <h3 class="product-name">Jinnie</h3>
          <p class="product-meta">
            For individuals and small teams. The waitlist is open at
            <a
              class="link"
              href="https://jinnie.ai"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener">jinnie.ai</a
            >.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="product">
          <h3 class="product-name">Sal</h3>
          <p class="product-meta">
            For enterprise.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
